text:
Why is indexing Strings slower in Julia compared with indexing Arrays? Aren’t strings just arrays of chars? Aren’t chars smaller than i64s?

```numalpha = Dict(0 =&gt; 'A', 1 =&gt; 'B')
X = rand(0:1, 1_000_000);
X_str = [numalpha[x] for x in X] |&gt; String

rand_ix = rand(1:1_000_000, 100_000);

@time X[rand_ix];
@time X_str[rand_ix];

# 0.000816 seconds (2 allocations: 781.328 KiB)
# 0.001581 seconds (4 allocations: 97.906 KiB)```

